@startuml
skinparam ranksep 45

!include ../../../../../../tooling/styles/plantuml/structural/class-diagram-style.iuml

title **The Diamond Problem**\nAmbiguity in multiple implementation inheritance

abstract class "Animal" as A #D5E8D4 {
  + breathe()
  + move()
}

class "FlyingAnimal" as FA {
  + move() : fly
}

class "SwimmingAnimal" as SA {
  + move() : swim
}

class "Duck" as D #FDEBD0 {
  + move() : ??
}

A <|-- FA
A <|-- SA
FA <|-- D
SA <|-- D

note top of A
  Common ancestor
  defines **move()** once
end note

note left of FA
  Overrides move()
  to **fly**
end note

note right of SA
  Overrides move()
  to **swim**
end note

note bottom of D
  **Diamond Problem:**
  Which move() does Duck inherit?

  **Resolution strategies:**
  C++ : virtual inheritance
  Java / C# : prohibit multiple class inheritance
  Scala / Rust : linearization / trait resolution
  Python : Method Resolution Order (MRO)
end note

@enduml

